postcontent: Up for sale is a beautiful CMP M1 GarandThis is a CMP Special grade rifle, built by the Civilian Marksmanship Program using only genuine Garand parts. This rifle was built on a Springfield Armory Receiver with a serial number that places it at October of 1943 production and barreled with a brand new Criterion barrel. Rifle comes with all the CMP paperwork, hard case, sling, and I'll throw in a couple En block clips loaded with new production PPU Garand specific 30-06 so you can get right to plinking on the range. I have obscured the serial number for this listing, the 2002xxx SN is enough to place it as an October 1943 production. Contact me for any additional pictures of parts draw numbers you may be interested in. I also have a milled SA marked trigger guard I can include. Both stamped and milled trigger guards were being used in 1943, some prefer the aesthetics of the milled trigger guards over the stamped. I personally hand selected this particular rifle from the CMP racks and sourced the Birch stock. Its been cleaned up, greased, but is unfired.
